1) SQL WHERE Clause:-
The WHERE clause is used to filter records.like
It is used to extract only those records, that fulfill a specified condition.

Syntax:- SELECT column1, column2, ...
FROM table_name
WHERE condition;

Ex:- SELECT * FROM Customers
WHERE Country='Mexico';

Select all customers from Mexico.
Note: The WHERE clause is not only used in SELECT statements, it is also used in UPDATE, DELETE, etc.!

1.2)Numeric Fields:-
SELECT * FROM Customers WHERE CustomerID=1;

1.3)Equal:-
SELECT * FROM Products
WHERE Price = 18;

1.4)	Greater than:-
SELECT * FROM Products
WHERE Price > 30;

1.5)	Less than:-
SELECT * FROM Products
WHERE Price < 30;

1.6)Greater than or equal:-
SELECT * FROM Products
WHERE Price >= 30;

1.7)Less than or equal:-
SELECT * FROM Products
WHERE Price <= 30;

1.8)	Not equal. Note: In some versions of SQL this operator may be written as != :-
SELECT * FROM Products
WHERE Price <> 18;

1.9)Between a certain range:-
SELECT * FROM Products
WHERE Price BETWEEN 50 AND 60;

1.10)	Search for a pattern:-it display all what we specified 's':-
SELECT * FROM Customers
WHERE City LIKE 's%';

1.11)To specify multiple possible values for a column:-it display all city wt we mention as per that.
SELECT * FROM Customers
WHERE City IN ('Paris','London');

